13/06/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Bulgarian Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov and his Greek counterpart, Yannos Papantoniou, signed an agreement Thursday (12 June) on defence co-operation. 
The document stipulates the training of Bulgarian forces for participation in peacekeeping operations with the Greek military, based on NATO principles. 
Defence ministers of Alliance member countries and NATO invitees are holding a series of meetings in Brussels this week. 
Svinarov said preliminary information suggests the NATO report on Bulgaria is positive. 
(Trud, 24 Chassa, Standart - 13/06/03; BTA - 12/06/03)
